docs.text: when you go to the movies as much as i do , you unfortunately end up seeing certain movie trailers one too many times .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: such was the case with frequency .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: every time i went to a screening , there was the frequency preview .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it looked awful .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it looked cheesy , sappy and ridiculous .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it looked like a flop .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: well , whoever put that trailer together should be fired , because in terms of pure entertainment , frequency is one of the best of the year thus far .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: frequency boasts a compelling story line .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: an occurrence of freakish solar activity allows police detective john sullivan ( james caviezel ) to speak to his fireman father frank sullivan ( dennis quaid ) through a ham radio , despite the fact that frank has been dead for 30 years .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: john is able to give his father information that prevents his death in a warehouse fire , but by doing so causes other changes .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: somehow , a serial killer's reign of terror , which in the original timeline had been stopped at three murders , extends to ten victims . . .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: including john's mother .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this is director gregory hoblit's third film ( the other two being primal fear and fallen ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: with all three , he's managed to attach himself to great scripts ( this one by toby emmerich , whose only previous movie experience was as a music supervisor on numerous new line films ) and add equally great direction .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: also , he apparently likes to have his films wrap up with a kick-ass ending .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: frequency is no exception , the ending is unpredictable and incredibly satisfying .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: hoblit is three for three , and i hope he can keep it up .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: now everyone can argue logic this and logic that all you want with the sci-fi elements of frequency .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but the fact of the matter is that time travel has never been achieved .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: who's to say how something works and how it doesn't when it's never happened ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: is it because we've become accustomed to time travel " laws " from other places like " star trek " and the back to the future trilogy and " quantum leap " ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: yes , if you sit down and think about it , certain plot elements in this film probably won't make any sense .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: most films are like that .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: don't let that dissuade you from seeing this fantastically entertaining film however .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when frequency was over , it made me wish i had seen it with my father so i could have given him a hug ( okay okay , shut up ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when you break it down past all its sci-fi elements and serial killer antics , frequency is simply a movie about a father and his son and the bond that they share .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's touching , it's sincere , and it's what ultimately makes this movie work .
docs.label: positive
